replies.bodyText:
Here is how resetReaderGroup() API on Client would look:
	1. ss.fetchUpdates();
	2. if (ss.updatingConfig==false) {
	  // this is a conditional update and so for 2 processes trying to do this update in parallel, only 1 will succeed.
	   2.1 val updateFlagResult = ss.updateState(ss.updatingConfig = true)
	   2.2 if (updateFlagResult == SUCCESS) {
		    set config.generation = ss.getConfig().generation;
		    set config.readerGroupId = ss.getConfig().readerGroupId;
		    val controllerUpdateResult = controller.updateRG(scope, rgName, config)
		    if (controllerUpdateResult == SUCCESS) {
			   ss.updateUnconditionally(config)
		    } 
		    // we set ss.updatingConfig = false in the following cases:
		    // (i) If both update to controller and SS have succeeded
		    // (ii) update to Controller has failed, & we never tried updating SS and directly landed here
		    // (iii) in the catch block for `controller.updateRg()` call, so if it throws an exception, we again set back "ss.updatingConfig = false"
		    ss.updateState(ss.updatingConfig = false)
	     } 
	     else {
		      // we're here because updateFlagResult==FAILED
		      // goto 1 
	         }
	} 
	else {
	   // here updatingConfig==true 
	  // goto 1 and keep retrying this reset in a while loop waiting for (updatingConfig == false) or bail out
	}
}

